Definition: immoderately desirous of acquiring e.g. wealth
Example: they are avaricious and will do anything for money; casting covetous eyes on his neighbor's fields; a grasping old miser; grasping commercialism; greedy for money and power; grew richer and greedier; prehensile employers stingy with raises for their employees
Synonyms: noun, attribute, avarice, act, avariciousness, covetous, covetousness, grabby, grasping, greedy, greed, greediness, prehensile, immoderately, desirous, of, acquiring, e, g, wealth, they, are, and, will, do, anything, for, money, casting, eyes, on, his, neighbor, s, fields, a, old, miser, commercialism, power, grew, richer, greedier, employers, stingy, with, raises, their, employees
Category: adj.all
